do deep research on :\cb1 \
\cb3 Her Holiness Sai\uc0\u8239 Maa (also known as Sai\u8239 Maa Lakshmi\u8239 Devi Mishra) is a globally recognized spiritual master, energy healer, and humanitarian, celebrated as the first female Jagadguru in over 2,700 years of the Vishnuswami lineage (en.wikipedia.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 \uc0\u55356 \u57119  Personal & Spiritual Journey\cb1 \
\cb3 Born: August\uc0\u8239 2,\u8239 1953, in Mauritius, into a Hindu family. She experienced mystical visions in childhood (en.wikipedia.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 Early Career: In her 20s, she lived in France, where she married, had two children, and trained in naturopathy, homeopathy, and osteopathy, running a therapeutic practice. She also served on the Bordeaux City Council contributing to EU healthcare reform (en.wikipedia.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 Spiritual Awakening: Became a disciple of Sathya Sai Baba and later reported divine visitations by figures such as Jesus, St. Germain, and Archangel Michael\'97prompting her to step more fully into her spiritual calling (en.wikipedia.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 \uc0\u55356 \u57235  Teachings & Leadership\cb1 \
\cb3 Holistic Wisdom: Integrates Eastern and Western traditions\'97ancient spiritual teachings, Western therapy, and energy healing(eomega.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 Global Influence: Founder of Humanity in Unity (Boulder, CO) and the Temple of Consciousness Ashram (Crestone, CO). She travels extensively, offering retreats, online courses, and public talks. There are over 200 Sai\uc0\u8239 Maa Awakened Living groups worldwide in four languages (en.wikipedia.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 Collaborations: Has shared stages with luminaries like the Dalai Lama and Thich Nhat Hanh (en.wikipedia.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 Author & Scholar: Holds a PhD in Spirituality and authored Petals of Grace: Essential Teachings for Self-Mastery (2005); also contributed to Grandmothers Counsel the World alongside Alice Walker, Gloria Steinem, and others (en.wikipedia.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 Trailblazer: In 2007, she was granted the title Jagadguru, signifying her as a world teacher\'97an honor not bestowed to a woman in millennia (en.wikipedia.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 \uc0\u55356 \u57101  Philanthropy & Legacy\cb1 \
\cb3 Founded the Sai Maa Vishnu Shakti Trust in India, providing women\'92s empowerment programs, disaster relief, medical camps (e.g., cataract surgeries, vitamin distribution), and more (en.wikipedia.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 Established the Sathya Sai Maa Shaktidhaam Ashram in Varanasi, completed in 2019\'97supporting ongoing humanitarian and spiritual work (en.wikipedia.org).\cb1 \
\cb3 \uc0\u55358 \u56792  Essence of Her Mission\cb1 \
\cb3 Her Holiness Sai\uc0\u8239 Maa stands as an Embodiment of the Divine Feminine, guiding individuals toward healing, self-mastery, and unity consciousness (en.wikipedia.org). With deep compassion and transformative insight, she supports a global community on a path to greater love and enlightened living.\cb1 \
