\f0\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb4 Excellent question. You can guide me to produce a deep research response by crafting your prompt in a specific way. Here\'92s how you can do it effectively:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 1. Use a Direct Command\cb1 \
\cb4 Start your prompt with a clear instruction. Phrases like these work best:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Do deep research on..."\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Provide a comprehensive overview of..."\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Conduct an in-depth analysis of..."\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Investigate the history and impact of..."\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 This immediately signals that you're looking for more than a simple definition or a quick summary.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 2. Be Specific and Provide Context\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 The more detail you give me, the better I can tailor the research. Instead of a broad topic, try to narrow it down or provide key areas of interest.\cb1 \
\cb4 Standard Prompt:\cb1 \
\cb4 "Tell me about the Roman Empire."\cb1 \
\cb4 Deep Research Prompt:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 "Do deep research on the Roman Empire, focusing on three key areas:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf2 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The economic factors that led to its eventual collapse.\cb1 \
\ls5\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The engineering and architectural innovations that are still influential today.\cb1 \
\ls5\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The daily life and social structure for an average plebeian family."\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 3. Ask for Analysis, Not Just Facts\cb1 \
\cb4 Request that I analyze or synthesize information, which pushes me to go beyond surface-level data.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Analyze the primary arguments for and against..."\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Compare and contrast the philosophical approaches of..."\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Explain the cause-and-effect relationship between..."\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Summarize the different scholarly perspectives on..."\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 4. Request Multiple Viewpoints or Sources\cb1 \
\cb4 Explicitly ask for a balanced view or for information from different types of sources. This tells me to look for nuance and to avoid relying on a single narrative.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0\cf2 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Do deep research on the benefits and criticisms of nuclear energy, citing arguments from scientific, environmental, and economic standpoints."\cb1 \
\ls7\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Provide a comprehensive overview of the Battle of Gettysburg, including perspectives from both Union and Confederate sources."\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
